This paper presents a reinforcement learning approach to decision making in dense traffic scenarios. The focus is on learning how to interact with other drivers with different levels of cooperation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to perceive the environment, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with decision making in a dynamic system, which could also place it in the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
